---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
import { projects } from '../../data/projects';

const project = projects.find(p => p.slug === 'global-release-engineering')!;
---

<ProjectLayout project={project}>
  <h2>The Problem</h2>
  <p>
    Sitecore's SaaS platform serves customers across US, EU, and APAC. A deploy that worked in
    us-east-1 could silently break eu-west-1 due to regional configuration drift, CDN cache state,
    or data residency requirements. And when it did break, rollback was a 45-minute manual process.
  </p>

  <h2>The Approach</h2>
  <p>
    GitOps-first, with automated health gates between regional rollouts:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>FluxCD Kustomizations with regional overlays — one source of truth, three deployment targets</li>
    <li>Canary gates using Prometheus metrics: error rate, P95 latency, SLO burn rate</li>
    <li>Automated rollback triggered by SLO breaches — no human required in the blast path</li>
    <li>Parallel region deploys where safe; sequential where data consistency required it</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Implementation</h2>
  <h3>GitOps Structure</h3>
  <p>
    FluxCD Kustomization tree: <code>base/</code> → <code>overlays/us-east-1/</code>,
    <code>overlays/eu-west-1/</code>, <code>overlays/ap-southeast-1/</code>. Region-specific
    secrets via External Secrets Operator pulling from AWS Secrets Manager per-region.
  </p>

  <h3>Canary Analysis</h3>
  <p>
    After each regional rollout, a 10-minute observation window runs. If error rate exceeds 0.1%
    or P95 latency increases by more than 20% vs. the 24-hour baseline, FluxCD automatically
    reverts the Kustomization to the previous Git SHA. Engineers get a Slack alert with the
    diff and rollback reason.
  </p>

  <h2>Outcome</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 my-6">
    {Object.entries(project.metrics).map(([k, v]) => (
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-[#27272A] bg-[#111111] text-center">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#3B82F6]">{v}</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-[#71717A] mt-1">{k}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>What I Learned</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Canary thresholds need per-service tuning. A 0.1% error rate is a critical alert for auth-service but normal background noise for the recommendation engine.</li>
    <li>GitOps rollback is fast but not instant — FluxCD reconciliation takes 30-90 seconds. For P0 incidents, we still have a break-glass manual path.</li>
    <li>The hardest part of global releases is the meetings, not the code. Coordinating EU data residency requirements across 3 teams is an organisational challenge, not a technical one.</li>
  </ul>
</ProjectLayout>
